text:
In version 1.1b1, you get a InvalidJarIndexException on line 129 in 
Category.java of you are using Log4J in an applet where the jarfiles use JAR 
Indexing. This is because that line tries to access a resource that does not 
exist in any of the jar files indicated by the index file.

This is what the line(s) looks like:

if(url == null) {
  // Is it under org/apache/log4j somewhere in the classpath?
  url = Category.class.getResource(resource);
}


More info on JAR Indexing:

   http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.3/docs/guide/jar/jar.html#JAR%20Index


An easy patch to the problem is to simply catch the exception:

if(url == null) {
  // Is it under org/apache/log4j somewhere in the classpath?
  try{
    url = Category.class.getResource(resource);
  }
  catch(sun.misc.InvalidJarIndexException e){
    System.out.println("WARNING!!! InvalidJarException");
  }	  
}
